        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:3:1:16:2",
        "text": [
          " سَأَلْتُهُ عَنِ الْمَضْمَضَةِ وَ الِاسْتِنْشَاقِ قَالَ لَيْسَ هُمَا مِنَ الْوُضُوءِ هُمَا مِنَ الْجَوْفِ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin yahya, from Ahmad Bin Muhammad, from Shazaan Bin Al Khaleel, from Yunus Bin Abdul Rahman, from Hammad, from Abu Baseer, ",
            "(It has been narrated) from Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup>, said, ‘I asked him<sup>asws</sup> about the rinsing (of the mouth and the sniffing (of the water). He<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘These two are not from the Ablution <span class=\"iTxt\">(Wudhu)</span>, they are from the (cleaning of the) inside’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Ahmad ibn Muhammad from Shadhan ibn al-Khalil from Yunus ibn ‘Abd al- Rahman from Hammad from abu Basir who has said the following: “I once asked abu ‘Abd Allah, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about rinsing one’s mouth and nostrils. He (the Imam) said, ‘They are not part of Wudu’.’” "
          ]
        }
